					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1358, Naḷa, Āśvīja, śu. 10, Gu[ruvāra]</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1436 September 20 Thursday,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that, while the <hi rend="italic">Mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Aṇṇappa-Oḍeya</hi> was ruling over <hi rend="bold">Bārakūra-rājya</hi> under the orders of the king, <hi rend="bold">Baḷabijjana-Bemmaseṭṭi-Nāraṇaseṭṭi</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">Baḷegāra</hi> community made a gift of some plots of land of specified boundary for feeding Brāhmans in the <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> at <hi rend="bold">Paḍuvakēri</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Basarūru.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
